A 37-year-old man has been arrested in Trans Nzoia for forcing his daughter to drop out of school to become his wife.  The girl, a Standard Seven pupil at a local school, has missed classes since March, according to a local chief.  Sources told The Sunday Standard that the man had quarrelled with his wife and sent her packing earlier this year.  Following the separation with his wife, the man turned to his daughter.    The police boss lifting the spirits of children living with disabilities  Woman who saved husband after snatching AK-47 rifle from robber speaks   How Trans Nzoia couple turned tables on an attacker and disarmed him  Woman mysteriously dies at her father’s gravesite An elder got wind of the incest and reported it to the chief who led police to arrest the man said to be a boda boda rider.  Matisi location chief Janet Nafula said the suspect is being investigated and will be arraigned.  The administrator said the girl had been handed to a rescue home.   Morning Express Sports Chat 9th May 2016 Trans Nzoia Sports Association  Mwanamke Ngangari: Seneta mteule Bi. Zipporah Kittony  Strathmore drill victim Esther Kidambi laid to rest in Aruba village, Sinyereri, Trans Nzoia County By Edward Kosut | 23 hours ago By Peterson Githaiga | 1 day ago By Nikko Tanui | 3 days ago By Peter Theuri | 3 days ago